<p>Hey <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-jesal-dave" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6635263); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6635263&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1594819025" alt="Dr Jesal Dave" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6635263)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-jesal-dave" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6635263); return false;">Dr Jesal Dave</a></span>: this is really not the best place to ask questions like this. You'd be best asking in either <tt>#site17</tt><sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-612705-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-612705-1')">1</a></sup> or in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/c-891087/help:questions-desk">Questions Desk Forum</a>.</p>
<p>That said, per the <a href="/authors-pages">Author's Pages</a> page:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>If you've created at least three successful pages (including SCP articles, tales, GoI-format documents, site dossiers, and artwork pages), please take the time to create an author page and take credit for your work.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Where successful pages are any that remain &quot;above -10 for 24 hours after having been posted.&quot;</p>
